Stand in the data form. . . . Near them, on the files,
Half buried a shattered visage lies, whose frown,
And wrinkled lip, and sneer of cold command,
Tell that its creator well those passions read
Which yet survive, stamped on these lifeless pages,
The hand that mocked them, and the heart that fed;
And on the metadata, these words appear:
My name is Fishmonger, Author of Authors;
Look on my Works, ye Mighty, and despair!
Nothing beside remains. Round the decay
Of that colossal Wiki, boundless and bare
The lone and level drafts stretch far away.’”[[footnote]]译者注：此处为一首诗歌，故保持原文。[[/footnote]]
